-- Greece's 2009 Deficit Revised Up to 15.4% of GDP, Widest in Euro's History
-- B y   M a r i a   P e t r a k i s
-- 2010-11-15T10:00:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-15/greece-s-2009-deficit-revised-up-to-15-4-of-gdp-widest-in-euro-s-history.html
Greece had the euro-region’s largest
budget deficit and public debt last year after a revision by
European Union authorities.   Greece’s budget shortfall last year was revised to 15.4
percent of gross domestic product from 13.6 percent, surpassing
Ireland’s 14.4 percent shortfall, Eurostat, the EU’s Luxembourg-
based statistics office, said in a report today. The debt was
revised to 126.8 percent of GDP, overtaking Italy at 116
percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
